<w:comments xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:r="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/relationships" xmlns:v="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml" xmlns:w="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/wordprocessingml/2006/main" xmlns:w10="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word" xmlns:wp="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/wordprocessingDrawing"><w:comment w:id="0" w:author="ckendall" w:date="2007-10-25T16:52:00Z" w:initials="c"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>Sal</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>I think we’ve attempted to hammer out the two components of OA before – 1) free 2) copyright (and I do this in my OA section for the EB).  I think we should focus immediately on the USAGE part</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment><w:comment w:id="1" w:author="ckendall" w:date="2007-10-25T17:01:00Z" w:initials="c"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>I think these next couple of lines could be summed up or reframed in the first para…keep the meat of this the data part</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment><w:comment w:id="2" w:author="Anita Palepu" w:date="2007-10-22T15:48:00Z" w:initials="A"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">We should live link to </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:ascii="Lucida Grande" w:hAnsi="Lucida Grande" w:cs="Lucida Grande"/><w:color w:val="000000"/><w:sz w:val="26"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>http://pkp.sfu.ca/?q=ojs</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment><w:comment w:id="3" w:author="ckendall" w:date="2007-10-25T17:00:00Z" w:initials="c"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">I think this para can come into play in the OA section rather than this one.  It goes backward toward the “why OA’ question. You could include a line about the DATA part but I think we should trim this of the basic OA </w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment><w:comment w:id="4" w:author="Anita Palepu" w:date="2007-10-22T16:00:00Z" w:initials="A"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>I think the Editorial Board and BoD should receive a document with the content from here on. We would have to craft a different introduction. We could publish the longer version as an Editorial</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment><w:comment w:id="5" w:author="ckendall" w:date="2007-10-25T16:58:00Z" w:initials="c"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>I always imagine that having access to data means that it can be (re)validated but ALSO that it can be manipulated to suit other patient populations or researcher needs</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment><w:comment w:id="6" w:author="Anita Palepu" w:date="2007-10-22T15:50:00Z" w:initials="A"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>This sentence does not make sense to me.</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment><w:comment w:id="7" w:author="ckendall" w:date="2007-10-25T16:59:00Z" w:initials="c"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>Might be worth adding a few lines on data mining.  TL could prob help – oops  - see it below</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment><w:comment w:id="8" w:author="ckendall" w:date="2007-10-25T17:00:00Z" w:initials="c"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>And neurocommons – see the science commons site</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment><w:comment w:id="9" w:author="Anita Palepu" w:date="2007-10-22T15:58:00Z" w:initials="A"><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">We cannot manage datasets at Open Medicine. This first sentence needs to be revised. </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>There are a number of issues that need to considered:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>Security</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>Handling requests</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>Monitoring its appropriate use</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Times New Roman" w:hAnsi="Times New Roman" w:eastAsia="Times New Roman" w:cs="Times New Roman"/><w:color w:val="auto"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:lang w:val="en-AU"/></w:rPr><w:t>Personally, I think the author’s institution should be archiving the data not the Journal</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment></w:comments>